Step 1: Download the IntelliJ Community version
Step 2: Open IntelliJ
Click New Project
Choose Node.js (or Empty project)
Set your project name: playwright-demo
Click Create

✅ Step 1 — Create Project Folder
Open terminal:
mkdir playwright-demo
cd playwright-demo


Step 2 — Initialize Node project
In terminal

npm init -y

This creates:
package.json

{
 "name": "playwright-demo",
 "version": "1.0.0",
 "description": "",
 "main": "index.js",
 "scripts": {
   "test": "npx playwright test",
   "test:headed": "npx playwright test --headed",
   "test:ui": "npx playwright test --ui"
 },
 "author": "",
 "license": "ISC",
 "devDependencies": {
   "allure-playwright": "^3.4.2"
 }
}

✅ Step 3 — Install Playwright
npm install -D @playwright/test

Then install browsers:
npx playwright install


 Step 4 — Create Folder Structure (1)
mkdir tests
mkdir pages
mkdir utils
mkdir test-data

Now project looks like:
playwright-demo/
 ├── tests/
 ├── pages/ —---------- means Page Object Model
 ├── utils/
 ├── test-data/
 ├── playwright.config.js
 └── package.json

 Step 5 — Create playwright.config.js
 Create file:
 playwright.config.js

 /** @type {import('@playwright/test').PlaywrightTestConfig} */
 const config = {
  testDir: 'tests',
  timeout: 30000,


  // 💡 FIX: Explicitly specify the 'html' reporter to generate the report files.
  reporter: 'html',


  use: {
    headless: true,


    // ✅ Capture screenshots for passed + failed tests
    screenshot: 'on',


    // ✅ Capture video only for failed tests
    video: 'retain-on-failure',


    // ✅ Keep trace on first retry
    trace: 'on-first-retry',
  },
 };


 module.exports = config;


 Step 9 — In the Utilities / Helpers

 In the Utils folder we have give the following :

 Create /utils/helpers.js:

 export async function waitForNetwork(page) {
   await page.waitForLoadState('networkidle');
 }

 Use in test:
 import { waitForNetwork } from '../utils/helpers';

 await waitForNetwork(page);


